## 📊 3. Finance & Wealth (The Brand Edge)

### Personal Finance — Tamil Audience Lens
- US credit system explained for someone who arrived 2 years ago (SSN, secured cards, utilization, AAoA)
- Tax basics: W-2 vs 1099, ITIN filing, what immigrants overpay every April
- Budgeting in two currencies (USD income, INR family obligations) — almost no one teaches this
- HSA, 401(k) match, Roth IRA — the "free money" most first-gen immigrants miss for years
- H1B / GC / citizenship financial implications (when to buy a house, when not to)

### Investing
- Index funds (VOO, VTI, VXUS) and *why three letters beat stock-picking*
- Bogleheads three-fund portfolio explained in Tamil
- The math of compounding shown visually, not as a lecture
- Why real estate is not always the answer for immigrants (vs. what parents say)

### Teaching Method (My Edge)
- **"Receipt Autopsy"** format — pull a real receipt/paystub/credit card statement, dissect it on camera
- Tamil-English code-switching the way my audience actually talks
- Frame everything around the *amma test* — would my mother understand this?
- Story-first, lesson-second — never the other way around

